    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dense, reddish-brown wood with black streaks obtained from the species Dalbergia nigra, native to Brazil. Brazilian rosewood is extremely rare because the trees were overharvested in the early 20th century. It is prized as a decorative wood, formerly used in the manufacture of furniture, cabinetry, and knife-handles. It is not a true Jacaranda.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
